%% xstream streaming - Scenario 2: Back-pressure (pause and resume)
%% After steady-state appends, BufferManager pauses StreamingService when
%% bufferedAhead > 20s and resumes when it drains below 8s (12s hysteresis).
%% The buffer.halt span is coalesced across rapid pause/resume cycles.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant SS as StreamingService
    participant BM as BufferManager
    participant V as video element
    participant ST as StreamRoute

    loop steady-state appends
        ST-->>SS: framed segment
        SS->>BM: onSegment(data)
        BM->>BM: appendBuffer, evictBackBuffer, checkForwardBuffer
    end

    Note over BM: bufferedAhead crosses 20s (FORWARD_TARGET_S)
    Note right of BM: open buffer.halt span (or attach pause event if coalescing)
    BM->>SS: onPause
    Note right of SS: suspend on resumeResolve promise
    Note right of SS: no further reader.read() calls

    V-->>BM: timeupdate ticks
    BM->>BM: buffer drains via playback

    Note over BM: bufferedAhead falls below 8s (FORWARD_RESUME_S)
    Note right of BM: attach resume event, arm 30s quiet-window close timer
    BM->>SS: resume
    Note right of SS: resumeResolve() fires, fetch loop continues
    ST-->>SS: framed segment
    SS->>BM: onSegment(data)
